  - TOOL_CALL: create_or_update_file({"file_path": "/tmp/expert_knowledge_librdkafka.txt", "content": "## Expert Knowledge for librdkafka Fuzzing Build Failure\n\n### Current Status:\n1. **Build Stage**: Docker image creation succeeded, but build process failed at environment setup stage\n2. **Error Type**: Configuration conflict between OSS-Fuzz build system and Dockerfile structure\n3. **Error Message**: \"Cannot use local checkout with 'WORKDIR: /src'\"\n\n### Problem Analysis:\n1. **Root Cause**: OSS-Fuzz build system attempts to mount local source code at /src, but the Dockerfile already sets WORKDIR to /src and clones the repository there\n2. **Conflict**: When WORKDIR is set to /src in Dockerfile and contains existing files (from git clone), the local mount cannot proceed\n3. **OSS-Fuzz Limitation**: The build infrastructure expects a clean /src directory for local source mounting\n\n### Dockerfile Analysis:\nCurrent Dockerfile structure:\n1. FROM base image\n2. RUN apt-get install dependencies\n3. RUN git clone https://github.com/edenhill/librdkafka\n4. WORKDIR /src\n5. COPY build.sh /src/\n\n### Pattern Recognition:\nThis is an **Environment-level** configuration error, not a Code-level compilation error. The issue is in the interaction between:\n1. Dockerfile structure (cloning to /src)\n2. OSS-Fuzz build system (mounting local source to /src)\n3. Build context setup\n\n### Solution Strategies:\n1. **Strategy A**: Modify Dockerfile to clone to a different directory (not /src)\n2. **Strategy B**: Remove git clone from Dockerfile and rely on local mount\n3. **Strategy C**: Use conditional cloning (only if directory doesn't exist)\n4. **Strategy D**: Restructure Dockerfile to avoid WORKDIR /src conflict\n\n### Recommended Approach:\n1. **Primary Solution**: Modify Dockerfile to clone to /src/librdkafka instead of /src\n2. **Alternative**: Remove git clone entirely and rely on local source mount\n3. **Fallback**: Use conditional logic in Dockerfile (if [ ! -d /src/librdkafka ]; then git clone...)\n\n### Implementation Details:\n1. Change: `RUN git clone https://github.com/edenhill/librdkafka`\n   To: `RUN git clone https://github.com/edenhill/librdkafka /src/librdkafka`\n2. Update build.sh to reference correct path: `cd /src/librdkafka` instead of `cd librdkafka`\n3. Ensure WORKDIR /src is set after cloning or use absolute paths\n\n### Common Pitfalls:\n1. **Path Consistency**: All paths in build.sh must match the new directory structure\n2. **Build Cache**: Docker build cache may need to be cleared after Dockerfile changes\n3. **Multi-stage Builds**: Ensure changes work with OSS-Fuzz's multi-stage build process\n4. **Backward Compatibility**: Changes should not break standard (non-local) builds\n\n### Verification Steps:\n1. After fixing Dockerfile, verify that local source mounting works\n2. Check that build.sh can find the source code at the expected location\n3. Ensure the build proceeds to compilation stage (past environment setup)\n\n### Expert Principles Applied:\n1. **Environment vs Code**: This is an environment configuration issue, not source code bug\n2. **Minimal Changes**: Modify only Dockerfile and build.sh paths, not source code\n3. **Path Discovery**: Verify actual directory structure before making changes\n4. **Build Context**: Understand that Dockerfile changes affect both local and remote builds"})
